{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}} {{Infobox non-profit | name =Lifeline Foundation | image = | caption = | type = | tax_id = | registration_id = | founded_date = {{Start date|df=yes|1996}} | founder = | dissolved = <!-- {{End date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location =Kolkata, India | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}} --> | origins = | key_people =* Suksham Singh (Director)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1090407/jsp/calcutta/story_10786298.jsp |newspaper=The Telegraph | location=Calcutta (Kolkata) | title=Dial 'D' in distress | date=7 April 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1100103/jsp/7days/story_11936513.jsp |newspaper=The Telegraph | location=Calcutta (Kolkata) | title=Look, Ma, I am dead! |publisher=Telegraphindia.com |date=2010-01-03 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref> | area_served =Kolkata; Nationwide | products = | services = | focus = | mission = | method =[[Telephone counseling]], [[E-mail counseling]] | revenue = | disbursed = | expenses = | endowment = | num_volunteers =38 | num_employees = | num_members = | affiliations = | subsid = | owner = | motto = | formerly = | website = {{URL|http://www.lifelinekolkata.org/ }} | footnotes = }} '''Lifeline Foundation''' is an [[NGO]] based in [[Kolkata]], [[India]]. It provides [[counselling|telephone counselling]] to [[Mental distress|mentally distressed]] individuals. It was founded in 1996 and has been noted for its efforts by the international [[Mass media|media]].<ref name="telegraphindia1">{{cite web|author=Our Correspondent |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1080310/jsp/jharkhand/story_8999803.jsp |title=The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) &#124; Jharkhand &#124; More hands to help pupils |publisher=Telegraphindia.com |date=2008-03-10 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ipsnews.net/2011/01/suicides-rise-across-india/ |title=Suicides Rise Across India &#124; Inter Press Service |publisher=Ipsnews.net |date=2011-01-07 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rebelion.org/noticia.php?id=120348 |title=Rebelion. Suicidios aumentan en India |publisher=Rebelion.org |date=2011-01-14 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mo.be/artikel/india-zelfmoordland-van-de-wereld |title="India is zelfmoordland van de wereld" &#124; MO* |language=nl |publisher=Mo.be |date= |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>
==Services offered== Lifeline Foundation operates a @g000in Keya ily [[Crisis hotline|telephone helpline]] to provide [[counselling]] to suicidal or other emotionally distressed individuals. The helpline is manned by [[Volunteering|volunteers]] and receives 20-25 calls a day. It also engages in raising awareness about mental health issues such as anxiety, depression, exam-stress and other issues in and around Kolkata by hosting [[seminars]] and [[workshops]].<ref name="telegraphindia1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1040910/asp/calcutta/story_3737823.asp |title=The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro |publisher=Telegraphindia.com |date=2004-09-10 |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/09/11/stories/2007091153681500.htm |title=Archive News |publisher=The Hindu |date= |accessdate=2016-12-01}}</ref>
